document_data.Description:
[[File:Witch of rashemen.png|thumb|''A [[Wychlaran]] and her guards.''|420x420px]]
The northern lands of Rashemen were predominantly barren, ravaged by strong, harsh winds, while the south was cooler with a more placid environment that was considerably more hospitable for habitation. It was surrounded by numerous other mountain ranges along with vast lakes and rivers, all of which provided strong natural fortifications. These features made Rashemen an ideally defensible region against the forces of Thay to the south or the nearby great [[barbarian]] tribes. 

Rashemen was considered to be more closely connected to the [[Feywild]] than any other location in [[Faer没n]].{{Cite digital book/The Masked Witches/Kindle|3125}}

document_data.History:
{{Main|History of Rashemen}}
Rashemen was founded in {{Yearlink|-4963}} by the followers of [[Shemen]], a chieftain of a [[Raumviran]] tribe, after his death.

Beginning in the 10{{th}} century [[DR]] and continuing on for centuries thereafter, Rashemen has repeatedly defended itself from multiple Thayan invasions.

During the [[Time of Troubles]], in the {{yearlinkName|1358}}, [[dead-magic zone]]s sprung up around the land and the Wychlaran had trouble contacting the spirits. Some witches and artisans went mad and were slain; some warriors also went mad, and it was thought they should also be slain. A few years later, [[Liriel Baenre]] utilized the ''[[Windwalker (artifact)|Windwalker]]'' amulet to set free the spirits and the land to normal.

Years later, the Wychlaran fought a vicious civil war against the ruthless [[durthan]] witches, in the conflict known as the [[Witch War of Rashemen|Witch War]].

